body:
### Version

Yosys 0.55+144 (git sha1 6440499e5, clang++ 18.1.8 -fPIC -O3)

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

Hello!

The [7-30 release of OSS CAD Suite](https://github.com/YosysHQ/oss-cad-suite-build/releases/tag/2025-07-30) (Yosys 0.55+144 (git sha1 6440499e5, clang++ 18.1.8 -fPIC -O3)) now has a bug where -1 sometimes expands to `32'd18446744073709551615`.

The bug does not exist for the [7-29 release](https://github.com/YosysHQ/oss-cad-suite-build/releases/tag/2025-07-29) (Yosys 0.55+115 (git sha1 8f6d7a304, clang++ 18.1.8 -fPIC -O3)).

Here are steps to reproduce:

```bash
echo '
module bsg_round_robin_1_to_n (
	ready_and_o,
	ready_and_i
);
	parameter num_out_p = 0;
	output wire ready_and_o;
	input [num_out_p - 1:0] ready_and_i;
	assign ready_and_o = ready_and_i[ptr_r];
endmodule
' > rtl.v

yosys -p '
read_verilog rtl.v;
prep;
write_verilog -noexpr -noattr -simple-lhs synth.v
'
```

Here is how I found this bug:

```bash
git clone git@github.com:bespoke-silicon-group/basejump_stl.git
cd basejump_stl

sv2v -Ibsg_misc \
    bsg_misc/bsg_circular_ptr.sv \
    bsg_dataflow/bsg_round_robin_n_to_1.sv \
    bsg_dataflow/bsg_round_robin_1_to_n.sv \
    bsg_misc/bsg_crossbar_o_by_i.sv \
    bsg_misc/bsg_round_robin_arb.sv \
    bsg_misc/bsg_mux_one_hot.sv \
    bsg_dataflow/bsg_serial_in_parallel_out_full.sv > rtl.sv2v.v

yosys -p '
read_verilog rtl.sv2v.v;
prep;
write_verilog -noexpr -noattr -simple-lhs synth.v
'
```

### Expected Behavior

I don't think I should paste the entire synth.v output, but here is an example of -1 correctly being expanded to `32'd4294967295`:

```verilog
/* Generated by Yosys 0.55+115 (git sha1 8f6d7a304, clang++ 18.1.8 -fPIC -O3) */

// ...

module bsg_round_robin_1_to_n(clk_i, reset_i, valid_i, ready_and_o, valid_o, ready_and_i);
// ...
  \$sub  #(
    .A_SIGNED(32'd0),
    .A_WIDTH(32'd1),
    .B_SIGNED(32'd0),
    .B_WIDTH(32'd32),
    .Y_WIDTH(32'd32)
  ) _3_ (
    .A(\one_to_n.ptr_r ),
    .B(32'd4294967295),
    .Y(_0_)
  );
// ...
endmodule
// ...
```

### Actual Behavior

However, here is what is actually generated. -1 is incorrectly expanded to `32'd18446744073709551615`:

```verilog
/* Generated by Yosys 0.55+144 (git sha1 6440499e5, clang++ 18.1.8 -fPIC -O3) */

// ...

module bsg_round_robin_1_to_n(clk_i, reset_i, valid_i, ready_and_o, valid_o, ready_and_i);
// ...
  \$sub  #(
    .A_SIGNED(32'd0),
    .A_WIDTH(32'd1),
    .B_SIGNED(32'd0),
    .B_WIDTH(32'd32),
    .Y_WIDTH(32'd32)
  ) _3_ (
    .A(\one_to_n.ptr_r ),
    .B(32'd18446744073709551615),
    .Y(_0_)
  );
// ...
endmodule
```

